goals.question: What is the distribution of flight delays?
goals.rationale: This tells us how many flights were delayed and by how much, which can help identify patterns and potential causes of delays.

goals.question: What is the average delay time for flights?
goals.rationale: This gives us an idea of the typical delay time for flights and helps identify outliers or extreme delays.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight distances?
goals.rationale: This tells us how far most flights travel and can help identify any unusual or extreme distances.

goals.question: Which airports have the most flights?
goals.visualization: bar chart of origin and destination
goals.rationale: This helps identify the busiest airports and can be useful for planning and scheduling flights.

goals.question: What is the relationship between flight distance and delay time?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of distance and delay
goals.rationale: This helps identify any correlation between distance and delay time, which can be useful for predicting delays and improving flight schedules.

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['delay'].plot.hist(bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.boxplot(data['delay'])
    plt.ylabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.xticks([1], ['Flights'])
    avg_delay = data['delay'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_delay, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Delay: {avg_delay:.2f} minutes')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average delay time for flights?")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    airport_counts = data['origin'].value_counts() + data['destination'].value_counts()
    airport_counts = airport_counts.sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    ax = airport_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("Which airports have the most flights?")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
